Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.69,0:03:30.82,Main,Gabiru,0000,0000,0000,,You can drink it or apply it on a wound!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.82,0:03:33.70,Main,Gabiru,0000,0000,0000,,The potion of total recovery: full potion!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.35,0:03:40.79,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,In contrast, Dwarven techniques \Ncan only extract up to 98%.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.79,0:03:44.00,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,The potions we can make are "high potions."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.49,0:03:48.42,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,A mere 1% makes a tremendous \Ndifference in potency.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.79,0:03:55.13,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,And now, at last, \NI've overcome that 1% barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.13,0:03:58.42,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,This is the result of my research!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.30,0:04:02.15,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? All right, I'll appraise it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.56,0:04:04.85,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.91,0:04:08.34,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Great Sage, use Appraisal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.86,0:04:09.61,sign_5967_48_Answer_,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\t(24,148,1 \blur3)\t(191,649,1 \blur0)}Answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.10,0:04:09.97,Italics_Top,Great Sage,0000,0000,0000,,Answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.44,0:04:13.57,Italics_Top,Great Sage,0000,0000,0000,,This potion is equal to a full potion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.35,0:04:17.65,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Well done, Vesta! \NIt's definitely a full potion!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.78,0:04:20.79,Main,Gabiru,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent work, Vesta!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.79,0:04:23.29,Main,Gabiru,0000,0000,0000,,Assisting you in this endeavor \Nwas truly worthwhile!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.47,0:04:25.65,Main,Kaijin,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go, Vesta!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.65,0:04:29.85,Main,Kaijin,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you were the right man \Nfor this kind of research!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.25,0:04:32.30,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you... Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.87,0:04:36.56,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, I really didn't think \Nhe'd be able to make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.95,0:04:38.93,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if we move forward \Nwith mass production...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.26,0:04:40.87,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I think if we sold this,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.87,0:04:43.43,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,it'd be a great source of funds \Nfor Tempest. What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.19,0:04:49.88,Main,Kaijin,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think that's gonna be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.61,0:04:53.57,Main,Kaijin,0000,0000,0000,,This potion is {\i1}too{\i0} effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.57,0:04:56.07,Main,Kaijin,0000,0000,0000,,We can't rely on it for everyday use.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.07,0:04:56.97,Main,Kaijin,0000,0000,0000,,Fine quality like this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.97,0:05:01.83,Main,Kaijin,0000,0000,0000,,is best reserved for high-level heros \Nin life-or-death situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.59,0:05:04.07,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.41,0:05:08.97,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,The potions sold in the \NDwarven Kingdom are low potions,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.97,0:05:10.54,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,which are mass-produced \Nby diluting high potions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.55,0:05:14.69,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say to \Nnegotiating with King Gazel
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.69,0:05:17.18,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,to have those low potions \Nproduced here in Tempest?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.35,0:05:19.66,Main,Kaijin,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that could work!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.66,0:05:22.02,Main,Kaijin,0000,0000,0000,,If we produce and sell the potions here,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.02,0:05:26.56,Main,Kaijin,0000,0000,0000,,the Dwarven Kingdom would only need \Nto procure the necessary ingredients.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.96,0:05:30.19,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I get it. That would \Nbenefit both nations, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.62,0:05:33.12,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Let's bring that up for negotiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.57,0:05:36.39,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You guys can continue \Nwith the production here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.39,0:05:37.30,Main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.40,0:05:56.96,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.96,0:05:59.09,Main,Souei,0000,0000,0000,,A new guest arrived in town,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.09,0:06:01.55,Main,Souei,0000,0000,0000,,and Lady Milim took exception to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.34,0:06:03.43,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Let me through.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.61,0:06:10.32,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Rigurd, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.32,0:06:12.41,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,G-Rimuru-sama, it's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.41,0:06:12.94,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.23,0:06:16.34,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,This is no cause for concern at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.34,0:06:17.44,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,No way! That's serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.99,0:06:25.58,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,This is who did that to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.87,0:06:26.76,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.76,0:06:28.44,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Rimuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.44,0:06:29.08,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.37,0:06:34.50,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,This guy thought he could mock us, \Nso I taught him a lesson!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.42,0:06:39.35,Flashback,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I am one of Demon Lord \NCarrion's Three Beastketeers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.35,0:06:41.22,Flashback,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Phobio the Black Leopard Fang.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.68,0:06:44.68,Flashback,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I am the strongest warrior of \Nthe Beast King's Beastketeers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.09,0:06:46.75,Flashback,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Nice town you've got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.75,0:06:50.81,Flashback,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Fit to be ruled by the Beast King, \Ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.03,0:06:52.06,Flashback,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you jestâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.44,0:07:07.91,Flashback,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,The Demon Lord Milim?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.26,0:07:12.00,Flashback,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Leopard Fang Flaming Palm!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.00,0:07:16.00,Flashback,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing \Nto my bestie's subordinate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.59,0:07:24.51,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I think she expects me to praise her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.31,0:07:27.76,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,And, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.16,0:07:30.02,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Should I really be praising her for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.85,0:07:38.05,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt she'll get away with doing this to \Nan underling of this Demon Lord Carrion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.39,0:07:43.28,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you promise not to cause any \Ncommotion without my permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.61,0:07:44.39,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.39,0:07:46.29,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Er, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.67,0:07:48.99,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah! This is different!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.99,0:07:52.04,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,He's not from this town, so it doesn't count!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.04,0:07:52.97,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,It does count.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.97,0:07:54.04,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.31,0:07:58.04,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,But since you did stand up for Rigurd,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.04,0:07:59.80,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just make you go without lunch today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.58,0:08:03.63,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,That's cruel... That's too cruel!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.01,0:08:07.09,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,This is all his fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.09,0:08:08.60,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,This scumbag!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.60,0:08:10.81,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,One hit wasn't enough! \NAt least give me one moreâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.81,0:08:12.27,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Wait! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.43,0:08:18.67,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,So, why did you come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.25,0:08:23.57,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph. You expect me to answer a lowly slime?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.51,0:08:28.87,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You may call me "lowly," \Nbut I'm stronger than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.17,0:08:32.74,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know this Demon Lord Carrion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.74,0:08:37.02,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on how you behave, my people \Ncould become Carrion's enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.38,0:08:42.01,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to be solely responsible for \Nantagonizing the entire Great Forest of Jura?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.26,0:08:44.22,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Hah! That's big talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.22,0:08:47.51,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,This whole town is loyal to \Na lowly monster like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.65,0:08:49.76,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Must be rough having nothing \Nbut weaklings around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.16,0:08:53.02,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get a big head just because \NLady Milim took a liking to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.28,0:08:56.90,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Are you talking trash about my friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.96,0:09:01.69,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Milim, stop. If you do anything else, \Nyou can kiss dinner goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.12,0:09:06.02,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I'll be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.94,0:09:09.70,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Now, it's true that I'm a slime.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.70,0:09:13.86,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,But it's also a fact that \NI rule 30% of this forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.86,0:09:17.58,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,and if you're really serious, we may \Nhave no choice but to declare war.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.92,0:09:20.70,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,So think carefully before you answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.50,0:09:28.09,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Carrion ordered me to come here and \Nscout some mysterious majin to serve him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.41,0:09:30.60,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? He must mean us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.68,0:09:36.60,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Milim wasn't the only \NDemon Lord who had an eye on that battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.97,0:09:40.11,Italics,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Damn that Carrion! He broke his promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.55,0:09:48.44,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I get the picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.44,0:09:49.83,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You can leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.83,0:09:50.45,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.45,0:09:51.33,Main,Benimaru,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.57,0:09:53.08,Main,Shion,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.33,0:09:55.92,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I can't kill him, can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.02,0:09:58.96,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the Demon Lord Carrion
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.96,0:10:03.59,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,that if he wants to talk, he can \Nchoose a date and contact us again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.73,0:10:12.97,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make you regret this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.30,0:10:21.31,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't look like he'll \Nrelay any message for us...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.72,0:10:26.74,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I want to know all about \Nthis Demon Lord Carrion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.51,0:10:29.97,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.97,0:10:32.70,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,We've sworn not to interfere with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.70,0:10:35.83,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,And there it is! She just confessed \Nthat there's some secret!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.36,0:10:39.11,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Did you only make that promise with Carrion?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.11,0:10:41.87,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Or does it involve other Demon Lords, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.87,0:10:43.50,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.50,0:10:45.29,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.29,0:10:48.38,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Carrion used his underling to \Ninterfere with you, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.20,0:10:52.72,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,And we're besties, so we \Nhelp each other out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.49,0:10:58.64,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,So I think it'd be a good idea for me \Nto know about the other Demon Lords.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.74,0:11:04.69,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't know what kind \Nof promise you made,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.69,0:11:07.95,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I might end up interfering \Nwithout realizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.43,0:11:09.98,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.98,0:11:12.03,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,But... Besties...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.32,0:11:13.07,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.77,0:11:16.12,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make a weapon for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.12,0:11:19.04,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm concerned for you as \Nyour bestie, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.34,0:11:21.04,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,A new weapon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.92,0:11:23.04,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.32,0:11:26.29,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing's more important than your bestie!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.95,0:11:29.61,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Too easy. She's way too easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.71,0:11:36.05,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Demon Lords Clayman, Carrion, Frey,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.25,0:11:41.13,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,and you, Milim, used Gelmud in a \Nscheme to create a puppet Demon Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.85,0:11:44.13,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,It was just a way to kill time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.13,0:11:46.64,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that's all it was to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.64,0:11:50.77,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,but since we butted in, I guess it's \Ninevitable that they'd target us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.38,0:11:54.48,Main,Benimaru,0000,0000,0000,,It seems likely that other Demon \NLords will become involved, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:56.34,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,What a predicament...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.68,0:11:58.83,Main,Rigurd,0000,0000,0000,,We must consult with Lady Treyni.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.19,0:12:00.55,Main,Shion,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.55,0:12:03.75,Main,Shion,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru-sama has nothing to fear \Nfrom any of those Demon Lords!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.11,0:12:07.30,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I've told you the secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.30,0:12:11.55,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Now give me my new weapon, \Nlike you promised, bestie!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.99,0:12:15.76,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,The storm that arose along \Nwith Demon Lord Milim's attack
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.16,0:12:17.97,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,would gain strength along its path
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.97,0:12:21.57,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,to swallowing up Rimuru's\Nnation and his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.88,0:12:28.02,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,One of the nations surrounding the Great \NForest of Jura, the Kingdom of Falmuth,
