Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.30,0:12:35.07,Italics_Top,Na,0000,0000,0000,,It was from this kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.07,0:12:37.58,Italics_Top,Na,0000,0000,0000,,that a team was sent to the Forest \Nof Jura to learn about the Orc Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.26,0:12:41.08,Italics_Top,Na,0000,0000,0000,,Led by a man named Youm,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.44,0:12:44.58,Italics_Top,Na,0000,0000,0000,,they're a rowdy gang, \Nbrought together by money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.58,0:12:47.67,sign_18332_205_Leader_of_the_Fr,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(527,1)}Captain of the Border Survey Corps  {\fs24}Youm
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.53,0:12:55.02,Main,Kajir,0000,0000,0000,,Bossâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.02,0:12:55.95,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.39,0:13:03.02,Main,Gido,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, this is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.02,0:13:03.84,Main,Eren,0000,0000,0000,,But, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.84,0:13:06.44,Main,Kaval,0000,0000,0000,,You guys... Whoa! Watch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.44,0:13:08.44,sign_18332_205_Leader_of_the_Fr,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs28\fad(439,1)}Farsight
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.89,0:13:10.19,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,How have you three stayed alive \Nso long by being this careless?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.99,0:13:13.61,Main,Youmu,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like some people \Nhave encountered a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.61,0:13:15.49,Main,Kajir,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do, boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.70,0:13:21.08,Main,Gido,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Wait for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.71,0:13:24.00,Main,Eren,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to butt in!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.00,0:13:25.15,Main,Kaval,0000,0000,0000,,We appreciate the help!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.15,0:13:26.55,Main,Gido,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.55,0:13:27.51,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.33,0:13:32.63,Main,Kajir,0000,0000,0000,,A Knight Spider?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.36,0:13:35.30,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,All right, boys, assume formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.26,0:13:38.18,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,Remove and heal anyone who gets hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.59,0:13:40.77,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,This is an order! Everyone stay alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.77,0:13:41.68,Main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.97,0:13:43.62,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,Kajir, take command.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.62,0:13:44.67,Main,Kajir,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.31,0:13:47.57,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,Rommel, use a strengthening spell on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.98,0:13:53.73,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,And you guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.17,0:13:58.68,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make you pay for getting \Nus involved in this later.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.93,0:14:06.47,Main,Gobta,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kaval! Is that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.51,0:14:08.96,Main,Gobta,0000,0000,0000,,Good to see you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.28,0:14:10.43,Main,Kaval,0000,0000,0000,,Gobta!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.31,0:14:13.83,Main,Gobta,0000,0000,0000,,You're fighting monsters \Nevery time I see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.83,0:14:16.05,Main,Gobta,0000,0000,0000,,Do you enjoy fighting that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.87,0:14:18.87,Main,Gobta,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll handle this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.30,0:14:21.80,Main,Gobta,0000,0000,0000,,You're for dinner today!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.09,0:14:26.71,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.93,0:14:30.56,Main,Gobta,0000,0000,0000,,These things are seriously \Ndelicious, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.61,0:14:36.40,Main,Gobta,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be ready soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.62,0:14:38.24,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.94,0:14:44.12,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the representative of \Nthis town... or nation...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.12,0:14:47.75,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,called the Jura Tempest Federation. \NMy name's Rimuru Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.16,0:14:49.92,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,You really are a slime!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.49,0:14:55.50,Main,Kaval,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Rimuru, there are some \Nfolks here we didn't see last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.64,0:15:00.27,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. This is Benimaru, \NShion, Souei, and Shuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.76,0:15:07.18,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,And that's Milim.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.91,0:15:16.65,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,So, the Kingdoms of Blumund and Falmuth \Nhave both come to investigate this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.99,0:15:17.48,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,We areâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.48,0:15:18.74,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.74,0:15:21.42,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,Why is a slime acting like such a bigshot?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.42,0:15:22.63,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,It makes no sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.63,0:15:24.15,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,What's the deal here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.15,0:15:26.08,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,Why are all of you okay with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.69,0:15:28.41,Main,Shion,0000,0000,0000,,You are insulting Rimuru-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.41,0:15:30.16,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,Shut your mouth, Tits!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.39,0:15:32.62,Main,Kajir,0000,0000,0000,,Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.39,0:15:32.62,Main,Rommel,0000,0000,0000,,Youm!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.86,0:15:33.83,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.83,0:15:34.91,Main,Shion,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.69,0:15:38.38,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about what Shion did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.78,0:15:41.22,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,She has trouble restraining \Nherself sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.22,0:15:42.63,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Cut her some slack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.63,0:15:46.51,Main,Shion,0000,0000,0000,,That's mean! I'm actually \Nknown for my patience!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.98,0:15:51.10,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,You've got a long way to go if \Nyou're that impatient, Shion!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.10,0:15:55.58,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,You're so short-tempered because you \Ndon't have an open mind like I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.58,0:15:59.21,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be on good terms with Humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.21,0:16:03.10,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I hope we can trade and network \Nwith you all someday, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.10,0:16:04.19,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Trade?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.19,0:16:05.16,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.16,0:16:07.94,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,We've actually entered diplomatic relations \Nwith the Dwarven Kingdom already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.94,0:16:09.41,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,With Dwargon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.65,0:16:14.06,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I think passing through this land would \Nbe more convenient for your merchants.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.06,0:16:14.92,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.23,0:16:16.95,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Now, wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.95,0:16:20.49,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that Dwargon acknowledges \Nthis nation of monsters as legitimate?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.76,0:16:24.18,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,I can vouch for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.79,0:16:26.09,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Minister Vesta!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.86,0:16:28.68,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Former{\i0} minister.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.08,0:16:32.18,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,What is a man of your standing doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.86,0:16:34.69,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,It's good to see you again, Fuze.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.35,0:16:38.30,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,What Rimuru-sama says is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.32,0:16:43.19,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,King Gazel and Rimuru have \Nentered into a treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.13,0:16:47.70,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Are you convinced now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.34,0:16:53.71,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well... If that is the case, we aren't \Nopposed to cooperating with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.90,0:17:00.86,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll need to see undeniable proof \Nthat you are, in fact, an ally of Humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.86,0:17:02.09,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,I assume that's all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.32,0:17:05.26,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sure. That's to be expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.26,0:17:06.90,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just fine with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.90,0:17:08.62,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll permit you to stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.62,0:17:11.30,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to understand \Nthat we aren't a threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.46,0:17:14.42,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Fuze-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.42,0:17:18.61,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,has the news that the Orc Lord was \Ndefeated already gotten around?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.88,0:17:23.61,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,No, only our king and a select \Nhandful of people know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.32,0:17:26.11,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I see. In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.30,0:17:29.69,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Youm-kun, want to make a contract with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.69,0:17:32.26,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What are you even talkiâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.91,0:17:37.60,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,What... might you be suggesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.60,0:17:41.19,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You said the Kingdom of Falmuth \Nhired you with money, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.19,0:17:43.76,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,So you'd just be switching employers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.17,0:17:46.56,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,To put it in simple terms...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.33,0:17:51.43,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I want you guys to be the heros \Nwho defeated the Orc Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.93,0:17:55.10,Main,Three,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.73,0:17:58.19,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Just say that we simply helped you out,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.19,0:18:03.78,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,and start a rumor that you were \Nthe one who defeated the Orc Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.35,0:18:05.68,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I figure, that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.68,0:18:11.84,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I can be known as the trustworthy \Nmonster who assisted the hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.51,0:18:15.00,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I think it'll be easier to \Nbefriend people that way
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.00,0:18:18.00,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,than if they think I'm some \Nmysterious, threatening monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.00,0:18:19.09,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.47,0:18:20.49,Main,Benimaru,0000,0000,0000,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.49,0:18:21.78,Main,Souei,0000,0000,0000,,Well put.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.40,0:18:32.01,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Have you gathered your thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.63,0:18:34.98,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru... No, Mr. Rimuru.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.07,0:18:39.92,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,This town is really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.46,0:18:46.28,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,After seeing all of them, I know \Nyou're not some evil being.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.10,0:18:49.28,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,We are people of guilty conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.89,0:18:52.08,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,We always longed to be free men.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.28,0:18:55.47,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,We accepted the mission to come here
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.47,0:18:58.21,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,because we planned to make everyone \Nthink we'd died on the way
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.21,0:19:01.09,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,and then head for some safe nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.37,0:19:04.51,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,I've decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.85,0:19:07.60,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,I'll trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.62,0:19:14.02,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to call you \N"Master Rimuru" from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.02,0:19:15.47,Main,Youm,0000,0000,0000,,I am at your command.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.82,0:19:17.97,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. I'll be counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.48,0:19:22.31,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, Youm and his companions \Nbegan training under Hakurou
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.68,0:19:26.08,Italics,Na,0000,0000,0000,,to look like heros.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.91,0:19:31.73,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,That didn't take long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.73,0:19:33.74,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't noticed, were you, Tear?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.35,0:19:37.57,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,I'm part of the Moderate Harlequin \NAlliance, too, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.57,0:19:39.25,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Have a little faith in me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.32,0:19:44.88,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just concerned you might go overboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.50,0:19:50.76,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez! Stop treating me like a child already!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.95,0:19:52.44,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.48,0:19:56.07,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,I received word from Myulan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.07,0:19:59.89,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,It seems Milim has taken quite \Na liking to those majin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.39,0:20:01.48,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.48,0:20:04.79,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,This is turning out to be more \Ninteresting than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.79,0:20:06.94,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,How truly delightful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.94,0:20:08.66,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's great,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.66,0:20:10.38,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,but what's really going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.38,0:20:13.66,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Is this majin really so amazing that the \NDemon Lord Milim would take interest?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.24,0:20:17.15,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,Only to the point that we \Nmustn't simply ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.15,0:20:19.76,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,He was no match for me, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.62,0:20:23.16,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,But then again, Laplace...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.53,0:20:24.83,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,What about Laplace?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.23,0:20:28.63,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we call it... an eeriness?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.08,0:20:31.61,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,He says he felt something of that nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.61,0:20:33.76,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.76,0:20:37.93,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,If a cunning guy like Laplace said so, \Nmaybe there really is something!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.09,0:20:39.19,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.19,0:20:42.96,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,I think we should find out why the \NDemon Lord Milim's taken such an interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.96,0:20:47.94,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we certainly will need to gather more \Ninformation and give it some thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.94,0:20:50.52,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we should!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:52.69,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,So, as for the results of my investigation!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.17,0:20:54.24,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.70,0:20:58.26,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Frey apparently has no interest in \Ngetting involved with the Forest of Jura.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.26,0:21:00.24,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,She seemed wary of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.56,0:21:03.56,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,It was almost as if she \Nwas preparing for battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.56,0:21:05.75,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,And did you find out the reason for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.14,0:21:08.46,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,I did! You won't believe this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.46,0:21:11.59,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,She was freaking out, saying Charybdis \Nwas going to be revived!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.82,0:21:14.22,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,Charybdis?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.12,0:21:18.57,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.01,0:21:22.47,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Tear, I have another \Ntask I'd like you to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.45,0:21:25.18,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you would!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.18,0:21:28.92,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,I've already called Footman, \Nso a little fighting is no problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.92,0:21:30.74,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,That's wonderful, Tear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.74,0:21:34.85,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,But I would like you to avoid \Nviolence as much as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.85,0:21:37.97,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,First, seek out the location of the seal
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.97,0:21:42.80,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,and find out whether or \Nnot we can tame Charybdis.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.80,0:21:44.82,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me, Clayman!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.82,0:21:46.26,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,The location should beâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.18,0:21:46.75,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,I said leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.15,0:21:49.41,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'm going now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.96,0:21:53.37,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,Charybdis, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.37,0:21:56.26,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,With power said to rival \Nthat of the Demon Lords...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.93,0:22:00.26,Main,Clayman,0000,0000,0000,,I truly look forward to \Nseeing what it is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.85,0:23:38.67,Italics_Top,Great Sage,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Evil Creeps Closer."
